## STATE CONTEXT
# Use this block when Cascade scaffolds the THIN Kinesis consumer, the
# state machine `inference-pipeline-<learner>`, or any per-record state
# logic. Applies from Day 8 forward.

- Triggered by: ESM on accelya-bookings-stream-<learner>

- Idempotency model — TWO GUARDS + STATUS LIFECYCLE:
    Guard A (Kinesis re-delivery):
      pk = f"stream#{STREAM}#{shard_id}#{sequence_number}"
    Guard B (producer-side dup):
      pk = f"business#{event_type}#{booking_id}#{event_version}"
    Status lifecycle:
      CLAIMED → IN_PROGRESS (fresh; stale @ 300 s → reclaim) → COMPLETED
    CRITICAL: only mark COMPLETED AFTER all side-effects succeed.

- Idempotency table: stream_seen_keys_<learner>  (TTL 7 d)

- Per-record state available to handler:
    shard_id, sequence_number, partition_key, arrival_time, data

- Partial-batch retry rules:
    - Claim idempotency key BEFORE any side-effect
    - Quarantine on ValidationError (NOT in batchItemFailures)
    - On unhandled exception: append seq# to failures
    - Return only OLDEST failure per shard:
        return { "batchItemFailures": [{"itemIdentifier": <oldest_seq>}] }

- THIN consumer (4 stages, in order):
    1. Idempotency-claim (ConditionalPut on stream_seen_keys, status=CLAIMED)
    2. base64 decode + envelope validate (raise ValidationError on fail)
    3. sfn.start_execution(stateMachineArn=SM_ARN,
                            name=f"enrich-{event_id}",  # DETERMINISTIC
                            input={...envelope, stream_pk, corr_id})
       Catch ExecutionAlreadyExists → idempotent skip (success)
    4. Mark stream-PK status=COMPLETED
    NEVER call Bedrock inline. NEVER write to S3 inline.

- Sampling cadence + HARD COST GUARD (in bedrock-enrich, NOT consumer):
    Default sample_rate = 10
    Deterministic MD5 hash on event_id:
      h = int(hashlib.md5(event_id.encode()).hexdigest(), 16)
      enrich = (h % sample_rate) == 0
    Hard cost guard: pre-flight check current Bedrock CW Invocations + Tokens;
                     if at cap, skip enrichment + persist enrichment=NULL +
                     emit EMF metric budget_guard_skipped
    Day 10 dynamic tuning: if rolling_5min_throttle_rate > 0.05:
                              sample_rate *= 2 (clamp at 100)

- Failure routing (reuses Day 4 PipelineError ladder):
    ValidationError      → quarantine/<learner>/stream_invalid/<reason>/
    MalformedRowError    → quarantine/<learner>/stream_invalid/parse_error/
    BedrockThrottleError → batchItemFailures + EMF bedrock_throttled metric
                           + dynamically lower sample_rate
    TransientError       → batchItemFailures
    ConfigError          → SNS escalate

- State machine: inference-pipeline-<learner>
    StartAt: BedrockEnrich
    BedrockEnrich Task → Lambda accelya-bedrock-enrich-<learner>
      Retry: BedrockThrottleError → 2s × MaxAttempts 3, BackoffRate 2.0
      Catch: States.ALL → ResultPath $.error → Next Quarantine
      Next: Persist
    Persist Task → Lambda accelya-persist-enriched-<learner>
      End: true
    Quarantine Pass state
      End: true

- ESM config (LAB-SAFE explicit defaults — set EVERY ONE explicitly):
    BatchSize:                       100
    MaximumBatchingWindowInSeconds:  5
    ParallelizationFactor:           1
    MaximumRetryAttempts:            3       (NEVER -1)
    MaximumRecordAgeInSeconds:       3600    (NEVER -1)
    BisectBatchOnFunctionError:      true
    StartingPosition:                LATEST  (TRIM_HORIZON for cold start)
    FunctionResponseTypes:           [ReportBatchItemFailures]
    DestinationConfig.OnFailure:     stream-dlq-<learner>

- Observability:
    Consumer EMF: records_in, records_quarantined, handoff_succeeded,
                  handoff_already_exists, records_failed, iterator_age_ms
                  Dimensions: StreamName, ShardId
    bedrock-enrich EMF: bedrock_invoked, bedrock_skipped, bedrock_throttled,
                        input_tokens, output_tokens, budget_guard_skipped
                        Dimensions: ModelId, Function

- Forbidden:
    - Side-effect (S3, SFN, Bedrock) before idempotency-claim
    - Reporting all failures (must be oldest only)
    - random.random() sampling
    - Synchronous Bedrock per record at full volume
    - Non-deterministic SFN execution name (no uuid4, no timestamp)
    - Accepting ESM AWS defaults (-1 retries, no bisect)

