## REVIEW
- 7-dim HITL checklist:
    Correctness · Safety · Idempotency · Observability · Cost ·
    Schema Discipline (D6) · Per-PK Ordering (D7)
- HITL_REVIEW-<artefact>.md committed; PASS at >=17/21 AND every dim >=2/3
- Schema Discipline checks (carry-over from v3): see v3 template
- Per-PK Ordering checks (carry-over from v4): see v4 template
- Streaming-specific REVIEW rules (NEW in v5):
    - Consumer is THIN (no Bedrock/SFN-side-effects inline)
    - All 4 stages in order: claim → validate → start_execution → mark_completed
    - exec_name = f'enrich-{event_id}' (deterministic)
    - ExecutionAlreadyExists caught as success
    - itemIdentifier = sequence_number (NOT messageId)
    - Report only OLDEST failure per shard
    - Sampling: MD5 hash on event_id, NOT random.random()
    - Hard cost guard env vars present + checked
- ESM creation MUST include all 6 explicit flags
- batchItemFailures KINESIS: itemIdentifier = sequence_number;
                              transient infra failures only;
                              schema/validation → quarantine + ACK
- batchItemFailures SQS: itemIdentifier = messageId (different from Kinesis)
- Region: every CLI example uses --region ap-south-1
- Synthetic data only.
